{"personas":[{"slug":"01-mutation-boundary-auditor","wave":1,"name":"Elena Marchetti","mandate":"session lifecycle ownership, external metadata write audit, patch-map escape hatches, CI guard coverage","questions":["Which production call sites still write lifecycle or identity metadata directly, and does each backlog slice name the call sites it removes?","What failing-build guard prevents new non-session production code from applying session patch maps or SetMetadata lifecycle writes?","How are doctor, migration, repair, and test exceptions bounded so ordinary callers cannot self-label into them?"],"red_flags":["production callers outside internal/session keep writing lifecycle metadata after command APIs ship","patch helpers remain reachable with no static guard","exception list grows into a permanent bypass"],"questions_text":"Which production call sites still write lifecycle or identity metadata directly, and does each backlog slice name the call sites it removes?;What failing-build guard prevents new non-session production code from applying session patch maps or SetMetadata lifecycle writes?;How are doctor, migration, repair, and test exceptions bounded so ordinary callers cannot self-label into them?","red_flags_text":"production callers outside internal/session keep writing lifecycle metadata after command APIs ship;patch helpers remain reachable with no static guard;exception list grows into a permanent bypass"},{"slug":"02-behavior-parity-guardian","wave":1,"name":"Natasha Volkov","mandate":"REQUIREMENTS scenario parity, regression prevention, characterization tests, proof freshness","questions":["Which REQUIREMENTS.md scenario rows does each extraction slice touch, and where is parity proven before the slice lands?","Are characterization tests captured before moving logic out of reconciler or manager code?","How does the plan prevent cited proof paths from going stale as implementation files change?"],"red_flags":["backlog slices lack scenario-row mapping","tests assert implementation shape but not product behavior","requirements ledger is updated to fit the refactor without owner-approved behavior change"],"questions_text":"Which REQUIREMENTS.md scenario rows does each extraction slice touch, and where is parity proven before the slice lands?;Are characterization tests captured before moving logic out of reconciler or manager code?;How does the plan prevent cited proof paths from going stale as implementation files change?","red_flags_text":"backlog slices lack scenario-row mapping;tests assert implementation shape but not product behavior;requirements ledger is updated to fit the refactor without owner-approved behavior change"},{"slug":"03-decider-atomicity-enforcer","wave":1,"name":"Takeshi Yamamoto","mandate":"pure deciders, optimistic concurrency, commit-event-intent ordering, stale fact defense","questions":["Can each decider run with only immutable facts and no store, runtime, config, or clock reads?","What compare-and-swap or revalidation happens immediately before mutation commit?","When a decision returns both SessionMutation and RuntimeIntent, what is the exact commit, event emission, runtime execution, and failure ordering?"],"red_flags":["decider queries store or runtime during evaluation","mutation commit is not conditional on the validated snapshot","runtime failure after durable mutation leaves no defined reconciliation or rollback path"],"questions_text":"Can each decider run with only immutable facts and no store, runtime, config, or clock reads?;What compare-and-swap or revalidation happens immediately before mutation commit?;When a decision returns both SessionMutation and RuntimeIntent, what is the exact commit, event emission, runtime execution, and failure ordering?","red_flags_text":"decider queries store or runtime during evaluation;mutation commit is not conditional on the validated snapshot;runtime failure after durable mutation leaves no defined reconciliation or rollback path"},{"slug":"04-event-delivery-contract-reviewer","wave":1,"name":"Amara Osei","mandate":"factual session events, idempotent subscribers, crash recovery, work-release guarantee","questions":["Are SessionEvent payloads facts with stable identifiers rather than commands to work, mail, trace, or extmsg?","If the process crashes after a durable session mutation but before in-process event delivery, how does a safety-critical subscriber such as work release converge?","Which reactions are critical versus best-effort, and is the recovery path documented for each?"],"red_flags":["event payloads encode imperative subscriber instructions","work release depends only on observing an in-process event","payloads omit identity context needed for idempotent replay or reconciliation"],"questions_text":"Are SessionEvent payloads facts with stable identifiers rather than commands to work, mail, trace, or extmsg?;If the process crashes after a durable session mutation but before in-process event delivery, how does a safety-critical subscriber such as work release converge?;Which reactions are critical versus best-effort, and is the recovery path documented for each?","red_flags_text":"event payloads encode imperative subscriber instructions;work release depends only on observing an in-process event;payloads omit identity context needed for idempotent replay or reconciliation"},{"slug":"05-target-identity-classifier","wave":1,"name":"Amara Diallo","mandate":"target taxonomy, alias precedence, conflict cases, caller behavior preservation","questions":["Does the classifier preserve direct bead ID, live session_name, live alias, named config, template target, path alias, not-found, and ambiguous cases with one precedence order?","How are overlapping alias, config name, and template name inputs represented without misrouting?","Which API, mail, assignee, and extmsg behaviors change when classification centralizes, and which tests catch each divergence?"],"red_flags":["classifier output is reinterpreted differently by caller","resolution order differs from existing target-resolution tests","historical aliases become writable live targets"],"questions_text":"Does the classifier preserve direct bead ID, live session_name, live alias, named config, template target, path alias, not-found, and ambiguous cases with one precedence order?;How are overlapping alias, config name, and template name inputs represented without misrouting?;Which API, mail, assignee, and extmsg behaviors change when classification centralizes, and which tests catch each divergence?","red_flags_text":"classifier output is reinterpreted differently by caller;resolution order differs from existing target-resolution tests;historical aliases become writable live targets"},{"slug":"06-api-cli-worker-boundary-reviewer","wave":2,"name":"Sarah Chen","mandate":"API and CLI projection, worker boundary routing, response compatibility, layering","questions":["Do API and CLI callers consume session-owned commands and projections instead of re-deriving lifecycle from raw metadata?","How does new cmd/gc production code stay on worker.Handle while session-owned commands are adopted?","What proves API response shapes and CLI output stay identical for touched scenario rows?"],"red_flags":["API handlers duplicate lifecycle logic from metadata","cmd/gc imports direct session manager creation paths outside allowed exceptions","target classification changes wire or CLI output without scenario coverage"],"questions_text":"Do API and CLI callers consume session-owned commands and projections instead of re-deriving lifecycle from raw metadata?;How does new cmd/gc production code stay on worker.Handle while session-owned commands are adopted?;What proves API response shapes and CLI output stay identical for touched scenario rows?","red_flags_text":"API handlers duplicate lifecycle logic from metadata;cmd/gc imports direct session manager creation paths outside allowed exceptions;target classification changes wire or CLI output without scenario coverage"},{"slug":"07-reconciler-runtime-fact-reviewer","wave":2,"name":"Liam Okonkwo","mandate":"reconciler boundary, runtime intent adapter ownership, fact isolation, health gate split","questions":["Which wake, hold, drain, provider-health, and progress decisions move into session deciders, and which scheduling or budget responsibilities remain in the reconciler?","Are work counts, pool size, runtime liveness, and progress facts precomputed by adapters instead of queried from deciders?","Can RuntimeIntent express adapter needs without smuggling provider policy into internal/session?"],"red_flags":["session deciders import reconciler helper types or bead store queries","runtime missing observations become durable session truth","wake eligibility and health gates share helper code that cannot move cleanly"],"questions_text":"Which wake, hold, drain, provider-health, and progress decisions move into session deciders, and which scheduling or budget responsibilities remain in the reconciler?;Are work counts, pool size, runtime liveness, and progress facts precomputed by adapters instead of queried from deciders?;Can RuntimeIntent express adapter needs without smuggling provider policy into internal/session?","red_flags_text":"session deciders import reconciler helper types or bead store queries;runtime missing observations become durable session truth;wake eligibility and health gates share helper code that cannot move cleanly"},{"slug":"08-migration-coexistence-strategist","wave":2,"name":"Ravi Krishnamurthy","mandate":"migration sequencing, legacy-new coexistence, rollback slices, worker-boundary collision","questions":["How does the plan sequence this extraction with the in-flight worker-boundary migration on overlapping cmd/gc and internal/api call sites?","During partial adoption, what prevents legacy patch-map callers and new command callers from split-brain writes to the same metadata fields?","Which single slice is independently shippable and revertible, and what proves it does not silently require the next slice?"],"red_flags":["two half-finished boundaries collide on the same call sites","old and new writers mutate the same fields with different validation","backlog item cannot ship or roll back without a hidden flag day"],"questions_text":"How does the plan sequence this extraction with the in-flight worker-boundary migration on overlapping cmd/gc and internal/api call sites?;During partial adoption, what prevents legacy patch-map callers and new command callers from split-brain writes to the same metadata fields?;Which single slice is independently shippable and revertible, and what proves it does not silently require the next slice?","red_flags_text":"two half-finished boundaries collide on the same call sites;old and new writers mutate the same fields with different validation;backlog item cannot ship or roll back without a hidden flag day"},{"slug":"09-yagni-contract-scope-reviewer","wave":3,"name":"Kwame Asante","mandate":"minimal vocabulary, facade creep, event-log deferral, backlog scope control","questions":["Which vocabulary types are required by slice 1 target classification versus introduced only for later slices?","Does TR-007 future durable-event compatibility shape current APIs more than today's in-process events require?","What stops SessionFacts from becoming a broad facade accumulating every field any decider might want?"],"red_flags":["unused vocabulary lands before any slice needs it","event payloads are contorted for speculative event sourcing","one mega SessionFacts struct replaces many operation-specific facts"],"questions_text":"Which vocabulary types are required by slice 1 target classification versus introduced only for later slices?;Does TR-007 future durable-event compatibility shape current APIs more than today's in-process events require?;What stops SessionFacts from becoming a broad facade accumulating every field any decider might want?","red_flags_text":"unused vocabulary lands before any slice needs it;event payloads are contorted for speculative event sourcing;one mega SessionFacts struct replaces many operation-specific facts"},{"slug":"10-operability-performance-diagnostics","wave":3,"name":"Ingrid Holm","mandate":"decision observability, trace and doctor diagnostics, fact read cost, event fan-out load","questions":["Can operators explain why a session was blocked, woken, drained, or closed from decider output and trace evidence alone?","What do gc trace, conflicts, and event logs show when a decision is rejected or an event is missed?","What is the reconciler cost of materializing facts and emitting subscriber events across a large city?"],"red_flags":["decider results hide blocker or wake-cause details","doctor or repair flows keep writing lifecycle metadata through legacy paths","per-session fact reads or synchronous event fan-out slow hot reconciler loops"],"questions_text":"Can operators explain why a session was blocked, woken, drained, or closed from decider output and trace evidence alone?;What do gc trace, conflicts, and event logs show when a decision is rejected or an event is missed?;What is the reconciler cost of materializing facts and emitting subscriber events across a large city?","red_flags_text":"decider results hide blocker or wake-cause details;doctor or repair flows keep writing lifecycle metadata through legacy paths;per-session fact reads or synchronous event fan-out slow hot reconciler loops"}]}
